<div id="main" class="col-md-9" role="main">

# Joins objects along a dimensions where dimnames differ

<div class="ref-description section level2">

FLQuant objects are joined along a single dimension, on which dimnames
are different. This is the reverse operation to divide.

</div>

<div class="section level2">

## Usage

<div class="sourceCode">

``` r
join(x, y, ...)

# S4 method for class 'FLQuant,FLQuant'
join(x, y)

# S4 method for class 'FLQuants,missing'
join(x, y)
```

</div>

</div>

<div class="section level2">

## Arguments

-   x:

    An object to join

-   y:

    An object to join

</div>

<div class="section level2">

## Value

A single object

</div>

<div class="section level2">

## Author

Iago Mosqueira (WMR)

</div>

<div class="section level2">

y <- catch.n(ple4)[2,]
